 {"id":"cass_memory_system-0ew.4","title":"Evidence-Count Gate: Pre-LLM Validator (P11)","description":"# Feature: Evidence-Count Gate (P11)

## Purpose
BEFORE sending a proposed rule to the LLM validator, check if historical
session success/failure counts provide enough signal to auto-accept or
auto-reject. This saves LLM tokens and speeds up the pipeline.

## The Insight
If 5+ sessions SUCCEEDED with a pattern and 0 FAILED, we don't need an LLM
to tell us it's valid. Conversely, if 3+ sessions FAILED and 0 SUCCEEDED,
we can auto-reject without burning tokens.

## Implementation
```typescript
interface EvidenceGateResult {
  action: "auto-accept" | "auto-reject" | "needs-llm";
  confidence: number;
  successCount: number;
  failureCount: number;
  relevantSessions: CassHit[];
}

async function evidenceCountGate(
  proposedRule: string,
  config: Config
): Promise<EvidenceGateResult> {
  // 1. Extract keywords from proposed rule
  const keywords = extractKeywords(proposedRule);

  // 2. Search cass for sessions mentioning this pattern
  const hits = await safeCassSearch(keywords.join(" "), {
    limit: 20,
    days: config.validationLookbackDays
  }, config.cassPath);

  // 3. Classify sessions by outcome (success/failure)
  let successCount = 0;
  let failureCount = 0;

  for (const hit of hits) {
    const outcome = classifySessionOutcome(hit);
    if (outcome === "success") successCount++;
    else if (outcome === "failure") failureCount++;
  }

  // 4. Apply gates
  // Strong success signal: auto-accept
  if (successCount >= 5 && failureCount === 0) {
    return {
      action: "auto-accept",
      confidence: 0.95,
      successCount,
      failureCount,
      relevantSessions: hits
    };
  }

  // Strong failure signal: auto-reject
  if (failureCount >= 3 && successCount === 0) {
    return {
      action: "auto-reject",
      confidence: 0.9,
      successCount,
      failureCount,
      relevantSessions: hits
    };
  }

  // Ambiguous: needs LLM analysis
  return {
    action: "needs-llm",
    confidence: 0.5,
    successCount,
    failureCount,
    relevantSessions: hits
  };
}
```

## Session Outcome Classification
```typescript
function classifySessionOutcome(hit: CassHit): "success" | "failure" | "unknown" {
  const snippet = hit.snippet.toLowerCase();

  // Success indicators
  if (snippet.includes("fixed") || 
      snippet.includes("resolved") ||
      snippet.includes("completed") ||
      snippet.includes("works now")) {
    return "success";
  }

  // Failure indicators
  if (snippet.includes("failed") ||
      snippet.includes("error") ||
      snippet.includes("broken") ||
      snippet.includes("didn't work")) {
    return "failure";
  }

  return "unknown";
}
```

## Integration with Validator
```typescript
async function validateRule(
  proposedRule: string,
  config: Config
): Promise<ValidationResult> {
  // 1. Check evidence gate first
  const gateResult = await evidenceCountGate(proposedRule, config);

  if (gateResult.action === "auto-accept") {
    return {
      valid: true,
      reason: `Auto-accepted: ${gateResult.successCount} successes, 0 failures`,
      confidence: gateResult.confidence
    };
  }

  if (gateResult.action === "auto-reject") {
    return {
      valid: false,
      reason: `Auto-rejected: ${gateResult.failureCount} failures, 0 successes`,
      confidence: gateResult.confidence
    };
  }

  // 2. Fall through to LLM validation
  return runLLMValidator(proposedRule, gateResult.relevantSessions, config);
}
```

## ROI
- Saves LLM tokens on clear-cut cases
- Faster pipeline (no network call for auto-decisions)
- More transparent reasoning (explicit success/failure counts)","status":"closed","priority":0,"issue_type":"feature","assignee":"FuchsiaPond","created_at":"2025-12-07T16:22:32.925118-05:00","updated_at":"2025-12-07T19:28:35.735671-05:00","closed_at":"2025-12-07T19:28:07.689228-05:00","dependencies":[{"issue_id":"cass_memory_system-0ew.4","depends_on_id":"cass_memory_system-0ew","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2025-12-07T16:22:32.926095-05:00","created_by":"daemon"},{"issue_id":"cass_memory_system-0ew.4","depends_on_id":"cass_memory_system-5eh.4","type":"blocks","created_at":"2025-12-07T16:23:19.037002-05:00","created_by":"daemon"}]}
-{"id":"cass_memory_system-0ew.5","title":"Curator Pipeline: Deterministic Delta Application (ACE Core)","description":"# Feature: Curator Pipeline (Deterministic Delta Application)

## Purpose
The "Curator" phase of ACE: apply validated deltas to the playbook
DETERMINISTICALLY. No LLM rewriting of the playbook - only precise
delta operations. This prevents "context collapse" where the LLM
rewrites everything and loses accumulated knowledge.

## Critical Principle
The ACE paper's key insight: if you let the LLM rewrite the entire
playbook, information is lost through summarization and compression.
Instead, the curator only applies specific operations:
- Add new bullets
- Increment helpful/harmful counts
- Replace specific content
- Deprecate specific bullets
- Merge similar bullets

## Implementation
```typescript
function curatePlaybook(
  playbook: Playbook,
  deltas: Delta[],
  config: Config
): { playbook: Playbook; applied: number; skipped: number } {
  let applied = 0;
  let skipped = 0;

  for (const delta of deltas) {
    switch (delta.type) {
      case "add":
        // Check for duplicates BEFORE adding
        if (isDuplicate(delta.bullet.content, playbook.bullets, config.dedupSimilarityThreshold)) {
          // Merge into existing instead of adding
          const existing = findSimilarBullet(delta.bullet.content, playbook.bullets);
          if (existing) {
            existing.feedbackEvents.push({
              type: "helpful",
              timestamp: now(),
              sessionPath: delta.sourceSession
            });
            existing.helpfulCount++;
          }
          skipped++;
          continue;
        }

        // Add new bullet
        const newBullet = createBullet(delta.bullet, delta.sourceSession);
        playbook.bullets.push(newBullet);
        applied++;
        break;

      case "helpful":
      case "harmful":
        const bullet = findBullet(playbook, delta.bulletId);
        if (bullet) {
          bullet.feedbackEvents.push({
            type: delta.type,
            timestamp: now(),
            sessionPath: delta.sourceSession,
            reason: delta.type === "harmful" ? delta.reason : undefined
          });
          if (delta.type === "helpful") bullet.helpfulCount++;
          else bullet.harmfulCount++;
          bullet.updatedAt = now();
          applied++;
        } else {
          skipped++;
        }
        break;

      case "replace":
        const toReplace = findBullet(playbook, delta.bulletId);
        if (toReplace) {
          toReplace.content = delta.newContent;
          toReplace.updatedAt = now();
          applied++;
        } else {
          skipped++;
        }
        break;

      case "deprecate":
        const toDeprecate = findBullet(playbook, delta.bulletId);
        if (toDeprecate) {
          toDeprecate.deprecated = true;
          toDeprecate.deprecationReason = delta.reason;
          toDeprecate.replacedBy = delta.replacedBy;
          toDeprecate.state = "retired";
          toDeprecate.updatedAt = now();
          applied++;
        } else {
          skipped++;
        }
        break;

      case "merge":
        // Merge multiple bullets into one
        const toMerge = delta.bulletIds.map(id => findBullet(playbook, id)).filter(Boolean);
        if (toMerge.length >= 2) {
          const merged = mergeBullets(toMerge, delta.mergedContent);
          playbook.bullets.push(merged);
          toMerge.forEach(b => {
            b.deprecated = true;
            b.deprecationReason = "Merged into " + merged.id;
            b.replacedBy = merged.id;
          });
          applied++;
        } else {
          skipped++;
        }
        break;
    }
  }

  // Update playbook metadata
  playbook.metadata.lastReflection = now();
  playbook.metadata.totalReflections++;

  return { playbook, applied, skipped };
}
```

## Auto-Pruning (Decay-Aware)
```typescript
function autoPrunePlaybook(playbook: Playbook, config: Config): number {
  const before = playbook.bullets.length;

  playbook.bullets = playbook.bullets.filter(b => {
    // Never prune explicitly deprecated (user decision)
    if (b.deprecated) return true;

    // Calculate effective score with decay
    const score = getEffectiveScore(b, config);

    // Prune if score is significantly negative
    return score > -config.pruneHarmfulThreshold;
  });

  return before - playbook.bullets.length;
}
