 {"id":"cass_memory_system-0ew.6","title":"Anti-Pattern Inversion (P3)","description":"# Feature: Anti-Pattern Inversion (P3 - 8× Impact)

## Purpose
When a bullet proves consistently harmful, instead of just deleting it,
INVERT it into an anti-pattern. This preserves the negative learning:
"We tried X and it caused problems, so DON'T do X."

## The Problem
Without inversion:
- Rule: "Use singleton pattern for database connections"
- Gets marked harmful 5 times (causes connection leaks)
- System deletes it
- 3 months later, someone proposes the same rule again
- The failure is forgotten, cycle repeats

With inversion:
- Rule gets inverted to: "AVOID: Singleton pattern for database connections (causes connection leaks)"
- Marked as kind=anti_pattern
- Future proposals matching this pattern trigger warnings

## Implementation
```typescript
function shouldInvertToAntiPattern(bullet: PlaybookBullet, config: Config): boolean {
  const { decayedHelpful, decayedHarmful } = getDecayedCounts(bullet, config);

  // Inversion threshold: harmful significantly outweighs helpful
  // AND we have enough data points to be confident
  return (
    decayedHarmful >= 3 &&                    // Minimum harmful events
    decayedHarmful > decayedHelpful * 2 &&    // 2:1 harmful:helpful ratio
    !bullet.deprecated                         // Not already handled
  );
}

function invertToAntiPattern(
  bullet: PlaybookBullet,
  reason: string
): PlaybookBullet {
  // Create inverted content
  const invertedContent = generateAntiPatternContent(bullet.content, reason);

  return {
    ...bullet,
    id: generateBulletId(), // New ID for the anti-pattern
    kind: "anti_pattern",
    content: invertedContent,

    // Reset feedback (this is a new bullet)
    feedbackEvents: [],
    helpfulCount: 0,
    harmfulCount: 0,
    state: "draft",

    // Track provenance
    sourceSessions: bullet.sourceSessions,
    sourceAgents: bullet.sourceAgents,
    tags: [...bullet.tags, "inverted", "anti-pattern"],

    createdAt: now(),
    updatedAt: now()
  };
}

function generateAntiPatternContent(
  originalContent: string,
  reason: string
): string {
  // Transform positive advice into negative warning
  // "Use X for Y" → "AVOID: X for Y (causes Z)"

  // Simple heuristic transformation
  const cleaned = originalContent
    .replace(/^(always |prefer |use |try |consider )/i, "")
    .trim();

  return `AVOID: ${cleaned}. ${reason}`;
}
```

## Integration with Curator
```typescript
function curatePlaybook(playbook: Playbook, deltas: Delta[], config: Config) {
  // ... apply deltas ...

  // Check for bullets that should be inverted
  for (const bullet of playbook.bullets) {
    if (shouldInvertToAntiPattern(bullet, config)) {
      const antiPattern = invertToAntiPattern(
        bullet,
        `Marked harmful ${bullet.harmfulCount} times`
      );

      // Add anti-pattern
      playbook.bullets.push(antiPattern);

      // Deprecate original
      bullet.deprecated = true;
      bullet.deprecationReason = `Inverted to anti-pattern: ${antiPattern.id}`;
      bullet.replacedBy = antiPattern.id;
      bullet.state = "retired";
    }
  }
}
```

